---
import ServicePage from '../../components/ServicePage.astro';
---
<ServicePage
	title="in Clapham"
	highlight="Outcome Measures"
	heroSubtitle="Effective rehabilitation should be measured externally and independently, not guessed."
	breadcrumb="Outcome Measures"
	seoTitle="Outcome Measures in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Objective outcome measures in Clapham. Independently validated tracking of pain, function and progress to guide every stage of your rehabilitation."
	intro={[
		"At Balance, outcome measures track progress objectively so we can understand your starting point, monitor changes over time, and ensure treatment produces meaningful improvements.",
		"They form a core component of rehabilitation planning, review, and progression, giving you and your clinician a clear, shared picture of how you are doing.",
	]}
	whenHeading="When outcome measures"
	whenHighlight="are important"
	whenIntro="Everyone benefits from a structured, data-led approach:"
	whenList={[
		"Clear visibility of improvement over time",
		"Accurate charting of intervention responsiveness",
		"A safety net for symptom re-emergence with direct therapist access",
		"Objective data for insurance or return-to-work and sport requirements",
		"Historical outcomes to predict likely improvement patterns",
	]}
	howHeading="How outcome"
	howHighlight="measures are used"
	howIntro="We combine patient-reported, internationally validated measures with objective clinical tests."
	howList={[
		"Questionnaires assessing pain, function, and quality of life",
		"Task-specific measures relevant to your individual goals",
		"Lifestyle and preference questions completed before your first appointment",
		"Evidence-based objective clinical measures",
		"Reviews at 6 weeks, 3 months, 6 months, and 12 months post-intervention",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Post-surgical rehabilitation, monitoring recovery and readiness to progress",
		"Sports injuries, supporting return-to-play decisions",
		"Chronic conditions, with long-term functional tracking",
		"Neurological rehabilitation, assessing balance, gait and independence",
		"General physiotherapy, providing clarity and direction for all patients",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What is an outcome measure?", a: "A standardised test or questionnaire used to assess your current level of function and track change over time." },
		{ q: "Why is this important?", a: "It provides objective evidence of progress, helping guide treatment and maintain clarity." },
		{ q: "Will I complete questionnaires?", a: "Possibly. They take under two minutes and provide useful insights into how your condition is affecting you." },
		{ q: "What physical tests are used?", a: "It depends on your condition, and may include strength, movement, or functional testing." },
		{ q: "Can I see my results?", a: "Yes. It's your data." },
		{ q: "Is this required by insurance?", a: "Sometimes. Objective measures support ongoing treatment approval requests." },
	]}
/>
